    "long_instructions": "### Focus on Reusability\r\n\r\nChoose a song to create a remix of. Design your code so it emphasizes **reusing functions** - taking smaller chunks of code and re-using and building-up to larger parts of a song. Your code should contain song snippets that are reused throughout the song via functions.\r\n\r\nIf you want to pick a new song, you can click the restart button in the upper-right corner [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=start-over-button). Some songs that might work well for this challenge are:\r\n\r\n- Gravity - Tinashe\r\n- Treat Me - Chloe\r\n- Beethoven Symphony\r\n- Born This Way - Lady Gaga\r\n- Scars to your Beautiful - Alessia Cara\r\n\r\nTo pass this level, you must call a function **4 different times** and use **10 different sounds**",
